This paper discusses a method for modeling uncertainty in rule-based reasoning, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the psychological realism of the method, which could fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Heckerman's modified certainty factor technique, which is a statistical method and could fall under cybernetics (cs.CY) or signal processing (cs.SI).
